-- BofA triples third-quarter loss due to forex legal expense
-- By Anil D'Silva in Bangalore
-- Thu Nov 06, 2014 04:58PM EST
-- None



Nov 6 (Reuters) - Bank of America Corp <BAC.N> tripled the size of its third-quarter loss to $232 million as it faced additional legal expenses related to its foreign exchange business.

The bank said it was in advanced discussions with some U.S. banking regulators to resolve matters related to the business.